CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 25, 1955, pg. 21 reads: "Wesley Pony Leaguers - This team of youngsters, sponsored by John Wesley AME Zion Church, are members of the Uptown Pony League where they have compiled a record of 4-0. Left to right, bottom row: Manager H. Perry, J. Walker, G. Goodman, L. Carmichael, C. Bibbens, G. Davis, A. Johnson, D. Carmichael and L. Richardson.  Back row: the Rev. A. Marshall, pastor; L. McDonald (in front of the pastor), J. Henderson, R. Terry, L. Yellows, M. Flournoy, F. Gumuca, D. Richardson, R. Sneed, Terry, and Manager J. Wright. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of John Wesley AME Zion Church pony league team, from left, first row: Manager H. Perry, far left; J. Walker, G. Goodman, L. Carmichael, C. Bibbens, G. Davis, A. Johnson, D. Carmichael and L. Richardson; back row: Rev. A. Marshall, L. McDonald (in front of the pastor), J. Henderson, R. Terry, L. Yellows, M. Flournoy, F. Gumuca, D. Richardson, R. Sneed, Terry, and Manager J. Wright
